  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "9. the north—(see on [925]Jer 1:14, 15). The Medes and other northern peoples, confederate with Babylon, are included with the Chaldeans.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "my servant—My agent for punishing (Jer 27:6; 43:10; compare Jer 40:2). Compare Isa 44:28; Cyrus, \"My shepherd.\" God makes even unbelievers unconsciously to fulfil His designs. A reproof to the Jews, who boasted that they were the servants of God; yet a heathen king is to be more the servant of God than they, and that as the agent of their punishment.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
